<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1456]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,302,829,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Remark.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[368,466,828,852]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[513,856,829,853]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[513,856,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Longchuanacris macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known as having very small external apical spines on the hind tibiae (
<bibRefCitation author="Mao" box="[434,688,864,888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Mao, B. Y., Ren, G. D. &amp; Ou, X. H. (2007) A taxonomic review of Longchuanacris Zheng et Fu (Orthoptera: Acrididae: Catantopinae), with descriptions of two new species from Yunnan, China. Zootaxa, 1467, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="2007">
Mao, Ren &amp; Ou, 
<number box="[627,688,864,888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); however, after being carefully re-examined, it was confirmed that the specimen lacked external apical spines on hind tibiae. The 
<typeStatus box="[895,993,899,923]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
was also observed to have a shallow incision at each cercus apex, indicative of faintly bifurcated cerci, a character ignored in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng" box="[158,373,970,994]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Fu, P. (1989) A new genus and new species of grasshopper from Yunnan (Orthoptera: Catantopidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 14 (3), 305 - 308." type="journal article" year="1989">
Zheng &amp; Fu, 
<number box="[313,373,970,994]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). From the 
<specimenCount box="[503,593,970,994]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="male">
<number box="[503,531,970,994]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="39.0">39</number>
male
</specimenCount>
specimens taken from the 
<typeStatus box="[897,945,971,995]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
locality, all individuals have small external apical spines on hind tibiae and clear bifurcations at the cerci apex, but two have only a very small external apical spine on left or right hind tibia, and other two individuals have only faintly bifurcated cerci. When comparing the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1078,1102]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[351,532,1077,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[351,532,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with specimens from the 
<typeStatus box="[826,874,1078,1102]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
locality, we found that they were the same taxon. Moreover, since the 
<typeStatus box="[385,433,1113,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
specimen was partially damaged during mounting, 
<number box="[1026,1054,1112,1136]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="73.0">73</number>
topotypes were designated for 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[506,587,1147,1171]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">SWFU</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1456]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName authority="Mao, Ren et Ou, 2007" authorityName="Mao, Ren et Ou" authorityYear="2007" box="[197,742,1183,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis box="[197,480,1183,1207]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Longchuanacris bilobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mao" box="[488,742,1183,1207]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Mao, B. Y., Ren, G. D. &amp; Ou, X. H. (2007) A taxonomic review of Longchuanacris Zheng et Fu (Orthoptera: Acrididae: Catantopinae), with descriptions of two new species from Yunnan, China. Zootaxa, 1467, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="2007">
Mao, Ren 
<emphasis box="[608,628,1184,1207]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et</emphasis>
Ou, 
<number box="[686,742,1183,1207]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was established, mainly based on three external features that distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[373,554,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[373,554,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: “male cerci with apex bifurcated”, “mid segment of antennae 
<number box="[1282,1366,1218,1242]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.3</number>
times longer than wide in male” and “mesosternal interspace 
<number box="[777,861,1254,1278]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.0" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.3</number>
times longer than minimum width in male”. Since the three features can be observed in 
<taxonomicName box="[597,781,1290,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[597,781,1290,1314]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the nominal species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1248,1290,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis box="[1121,1248,1290,1314]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the differences between them become blurred. In other words, there is no difference between them on species status, differing only in secondary characters. Based on the substantial similarities in the external morphology and male genitalia structures, 
<taxonomicName box="[276,457,1396,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[276,457,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[515,640,1396,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis box="[515,640,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. bilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are thus proven to be the conspecific. In this paper, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mao, Ren et Ou, 2007" authorityName="Mao, Ren et Ou" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobata">
<emphasis box="[1244,1369,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. bilobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mao" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Mao, B. Y., Ren, G. D. &amp; Ou, X. H. (2007) A taxonomic review of Longchuanacris Zheng et Fu (Orthoptera: Acrididae: Catantopinae), with descriptions of two new species from Yunnan, China. Zootaxa, 1467, 51 - 62." type="journal article" year="2007">
Mao, Ren 
<emphasis box="[203,223,1433,1456]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et</emphasis>
Ou, 
<number box="[278,334,1431,1455]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed as a new junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zheng et Fu, 1989" authorityName="Zheng et Fu" authorityYear="1989" box="[794,1189,1431,1456]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Longchuanacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrofurcula">
<emphasis box="[794,973,1431,1456]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. macrofurcula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng" box="[981,1189,1431,1456]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Fu, P. (1989) A new genus and new species of grasshopper from Yunnan (Orthoptera: Catantopidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 14 (3), 305 - 308." type="journal article" year="1989">
Zheng 
<emphasis box="[1059,1079,1433,1456]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et</emphasis>
Fu, 
<number box="[1130,1189,1431,1455]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
